<item>
            <title>[JDK-8334239] Introduce macro for ubsan method/function exclusions</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8334239</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>A number of functions/methods have to be excluded from ubsan detection (e.g. because they do things that ubsan warns about, however it is still valid what is done there).&lt;br/&gt;
We can simplify this by introducing a macro (similar to asan-related ATTRIBUTE_NO_ASAN, see address.hpp).&lt;br/&gt;
Currently something like  this is used :&lt;br/&gt;
#if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__)&lt;br/&gt;
__attribute__((no_sanitize(&amp;quot;undefined&amp;quot;)))&lt;br/&gt;
#endif</description>
